I was trying to say was that coming up with a hard list such as the one Biggerin suggested assumes that we do, in fact, know all those variables.<br>
<br>
What I'd do is continue to analyze the data we get as thoroughly as possible, separating out the different damage sources whenever possible.<br>
<br>
The sum of mage damage might be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> mage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->=<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> petmelee+magnukes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, whereas a monk might be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> monk=melee</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, where <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> melee=petmelee*k</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  A wizard might be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> wizard=nukes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, where <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> nukes=magnukes*c</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Analysis of log data can help us find reasonable values for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> k</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> c</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> seperately, based on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> melee</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and [/i]nuke[/i] relationships as opposed to the more abstract <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> mage, monk, and wizard</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> relationships.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Goladus I think you idea doesnt take into account all the mages that feel they are not doing enough damage solo/grouping.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You are right about soloing.  However, in all honestly I was thinking more about normal grouping than raids anyway.  I've found that in groups with no enchanter, I totally fugging own.  Only monks and rogues can touch my damage output unhasted.<br>
<br>
However, aside from the issue that my suggestion involves a new spell, which Razamatazz seems to think an unlikely solution, and I sort of agree with him, my suggestion is an elegant solution to the problem presented.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Raids are a very small part of the game for most people that play. That fix wont help those others that feel mages need damage upgrades.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Right and right.  However, it is my personal opinion that many of the people that feel we need damage upgrades underestimate themselves.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also why does Verant need to give us lower haste buff then burnout that allows us to stack haste with enchanters? They can give mages a 200% haste buff, unless pet pathing, aggro on raids is fixed no guild leader is going to risk a pet causing the death of 40 people.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->First, I sort of need you to clarify what you mean by fixing aggro.  Secondly, I must disagree with you concerning pets on raids.  My guild is currently trying to figure out how to kill Vindicator, we've almost got him.. I'm fairly sure next time we try we'll win... and hell yes the raid leader wants pets dealing damage.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also as I have said in the past I want to solo better. I dont agree that Verant wont do anything to help us solo better. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Actually, I don't think I ever said that verant wouldn't add anything to help us solo better.  Raz listed a bunch of cons, however, to increasing pet power, and I offered a solution that dealt with as many of these cons as possible.<br>
<br>
In fact, Verant <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> has</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> done things to help us solo better:<br>
<br>
1.  Epic pet<br>
2.  Boots of Bladecalling<br>
3.  Transons Mana Regen<br>
4.  Rod of Mystical Transvergence<br>
5.  Flowing Thought Items<br>
6.  Water Elemental Form<br>
7.  Mend Companion(ok this isn't really useful with the 144min refresh, but it's a step)<br>
8.  A 65 AC robe<br>
<br>
So yes, you're right, I don't think Verant is that worried about soloing better.  I hesitate to quote Absor in public, because people are so quick to twist and misunderstand what is said, but it seemed pretty clear to me that he'd actually agree with you Wezloc.<br>
<br>
However, I also agree with Raz when he writes:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Anything whose <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>sole</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> purpose is to improve soloing will not even be considered.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#333333>(2/7/02 3:16:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Increased Pet Strength, Summary Pro and Con</span><hr size=1> Raz you kinda miss quoted me.<br>
