<br>
Indifferent pets will make no alterations to the way pets aggro. It will make changes to the way things aggro on them. Consiquentally, if you get hit, or even swung at, your pet instantly hates anything that tried to hurt you, and as you near, your pet will attack. It will not change the way social mobs react to pets once aggro'd. It will not change any behavior while nearby mobs/pets are aggro'd. It changes NON-combat faction standings between pets and everything else. Once you (get hit, cast on, swung at, looked at funny, or order an attack) or your pet engage in combat, things would behave as normal, since standard 'faction' rules of if they like you do not apply then.<br>
<br>
The only worry in the situation you brought up: If you get aggro yet do not get hit, and lead the mob over towards the pet. Pet will not aggro mob, but then, the mob probably won't aggro the pet unless the pet does something to cause the mob to switch targets (does some damage, taunts, etc). In that situation, if you're that much in control, why not hit /pet attack as normal? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrumples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grumples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#333333>(2/7/02 10:21:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Increased Pet Strength, Summary Pro and Con</span><hr size=1> Actually, I meant if the pet was already fighting another.<br>
<br>
e.g., farming Droga.  Pet is on a goblin, another goblin attacks me.  I run past the pet and the goblin will almost always stop and fight my pet instead of chasing me past it.<br>
