<br>
Of course, if you're in, say, Burning Woods fighting wasps and you agro a sarnak, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> then</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you would surely be screwed: your pet is busy with the wasp.  Currently you could train the sarnak onto the pet.  If the pet is indifferent, the sarnak would ignore it.  You might have a hard time getting the pet to switch targets.  Given our lack of defense options, we'd be screwed.<br>
<br>
It's a fairly rare event, suddenly fighting 2 mobs of 2 different factions (or 2 non-social agro mobs), but I still prefer increasing pet strength.  The only side effect to that is that we might become too powerful.  I fail to see the problem there.  God knows it worked for other classes.<br>
