If pet is fighting mob A and mob B wanders by and sees you it attacks.  It doesnt attack pet because it sees pet as indifferent so now you have a mob on you that you cant train on the pet because it wont attack pet unless it is attacked by the pet first. Now when I am soloing it is very hard to pull a pet off another mob that is attacking it so that it attacks the mob that is on me. Easiest way I have found is just to train mob onto pet. Normally if I havent done any damage to the added mob it will start fighting pet. The pet must work like this if this change is to help in raids. Pet gets AoE feared by a mob and moves around the zone. It doesn't aggro anything because everything sees him as indifferent. This would eliminate farming and would make soloing/escaping that much harder.<br>
